data.chText: 不受控制
data.enText: not controlled

data.chText: 能随自己意愿的；随心所欲的
data.enText: not under the control or in the power of sb else; able to do what you want

data.chText: 我没有雄心大志，只求自由自在地过幸福生活。
data.enText: I have no ambitions other than to have a happy life and be free.

data.chText: 学生在最后一学年可以自由选修课程。
data.enText: Students have a free choice of courses in their final year.

data.chText: 你来去自由。
data.enText: You are free to come and go as you please.

data.chText: “我能用一下电话吗？”“请便吧。”
data.enText: ‘Can I use the phone?’ ‘Please, feel free (= of course you can use it) .’

data.chText: 不受限制的；不受约束的；言行自由的
data.enText: not restricted or controlled by anyone else; able to do or say what you want

data.chText: 人们呼吁要有充分言论自由和新闻自由的真正民主。
data.enText: A true democracy complete with free speech and a free press was called for.

data.chText: 该国的第一次自由选举
data.enText: the country's first free election

data.chText: 他们让我自由查阅所有档案资料。
data.enText: They gave me free access to all the files.

data.enText: not prisoner

data.chText: 自由的（不是囚犯或奴隶）
data.enText: not a prisoner or slave

data.chText: 他获释出狱，成为自由人。
data.enText: He walked out of jail a free man .

data.enText: Admission is free.

data.chText: 购买一册就可以得到一份免费好礼。

data.chText: 你不能指望人工作不要报酬。

data.enText: free from difficulty/doubt/fear

data.chText: 不含人工色素和人工调味料

data.chText: 她终于设法挣脱了。

data.enText: The designer was given free rein.

data.chText: 剧本允许她充分展现她那夸张的表演风格。
data.enText: The script allows full rein to her larger-than-life acting style.

data.chText: 囚犯
data.enText: prisoner

data.chText: 释放；使自由
data.enText: to allow sb to leave prison or somewhere they have been kept against their will

data.chText: 至五月底，估计2 000名政治犯中有近100人已经获释。
data.enText: By the end of May nearly 100 of an estimated 2 000 political prisoners had been freed.

data.chText: 劫持者已同意再释放十名人质。
data.enText: The hijackers agreed to free a further ten hostages.

data.chText: 被困住的人 / 物
data.enText: sb/sth trapped

data.chText: 解放；使摆脱
data.enText: to move sb/sth that is caught or fixed on sth

data.chText: 有三人被救出残骸。
data.enText: Three people were freed from the wreckage.

data.chText: 她挣扎着以求脱身。
data.enText: She struggled to free herself.

data.chText: 去除某物
data.enText: remove sth

data.chText: 解除（或去除、清除）
data.enText: to remove sth that is unpleasant or not wanted from sb/sth

data.chText: 这些锻炼可使紧张的身体放松。
data.enText: These exercises help free the body of tension.

data.chText: 警方决心消灭该城镇的暴力犯罪。
data.enText: The police are determined to free the town of violent crime.

data.chText: 这个中心的目的是使年轻人解除对毒品的依赖。
data.enText: The centre aims to free young people from dependency on drugs.

data.chText: 使现成可用

data.enText: to make sb/sth available for a particular purpose

data.chText: 我们每周都腾出时间开一次项目会议。
data.enText: We freed time each week for a project meeting.

data.chText: 政府保证调拨更多资源用于教育。
data.enText: The government has promised to free up more resources for education.

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

trans: 开放，放开（市场、经济或制度）

example: the home of the free and the brave
release the holdings in the dictator's bank account
I absolve you from this responsibility
free a path across the cluttered floor

tr: remove or force out from a position
example: The dentist dislodged the piece of food that had been stuck under my gums
He finally could free the legs of the earthquake victim who was buried in the rubble

tr: release (gas or energy) as a result of a chemical reaction or physical decomposition
part with a possession or right
example: I am relinquishing my bedroom to the long-term house guest
resign a claim to the throne
release the list with the names of the prisoners

tr: grant relief or an exemption from a rule or requirement to
example: She exempted me from the exam
a loose interpretation of what she had been told
a free translation of the poem
the sentence was devoid of meaning

tr: unconstrained or not chemically bound in a molecule or not fixed and capable of relatively unrestricted motion

example: the detached shutter fell on him
he pulled his arm free and ran
feel free to stay as long as you wish
after the Civil War he was a free man

tr: not taken up by scheduled activities

example: cows in India are running loose

value.def: If something is free, you can have it or use it without paying for it.

example.ex: The seminars are free, with lunch provided.
example.tran: 研讨会不收会务费，而且还提供午餐。

example.ex: ...a free brochure with details of gift vouchers.
example.tran: 内有礼券详情的免费宣传册

value.def: Someone or something that is free is not restricted, controlled, or limited, for example by rules, customs, or other people.

example.ex: The government will be free to pursue its economic policies...
example.tran: 政府将可不受限制地实行其经济政策。

example.ex: The elections were free and fair...
example.tran: 选举是自由公正的。

example.ex: Economists argued that freer markets would quickly revive the region's economy...
example.tran: 经济学家认为更加自由的市场将使这个地区的经济迅速复苏。

example.ex: He fears that until state subsidies are removed, Russia will never have a truly free press...
example.tran: 他担心在取消国家补助之前，俄罗斯将根本不会有真正自由的媒体。

example.ex: Dogs were allowed to roam free and 48 sheep were killed.
example.tran: 没有对狗加以约束而让它们四处乱跑，结果有48只羊被咬死。

value.tran: 自由的;不受约束的;没有限制的

example.ex: They cast their votes freely and without coercion on election day...
example.tran: 选举日那天他们自由地进行了投票，没有受到胁迫。

example.ex: Merchandise can now circulate freely among the EU countries.
example.tran: 商品现在可以在欧盟各国自由流通。

value.def: If you free someone of something that is unpleasant or restricting, you remove it from them.

example.ex: It will free us of a whole lot of debt...
example.tran: 它会使我们摆脱巨额债务。

example.ex: The 30-year-old star is trying to free himself from his recording contract.
example.tran: 这位30 岁的明星正试图从他的唱片合约中脱身。

value.def: Someone who is free is no longer a prisoner or a slave.

example.ex: He walked from the court house a free man...
example.tran: 他以自由之身走出了法院。

example.ex: More than ninety prisoners have been set free so far under a government amnesty.
example.tran: 目前已有 90 多名犯人因为一项政府特赦获得自由。

gramarinfo.label: ADJ n, v-link ADJ, ADJ after v

value.tran: (人身)自由的;不受监禁(或奴役)的

value.def: To free a prisoner or a slave means to let them go or release them from prison.

example.ex: Israel is set to free more Lebanese prisoners...
example.tran: 以色列准备释放更多的黎巴嫩犯人。

example.ex: The act had a specific intent, to protect freed slaves from white mobs.
example.tran: 这项法案有明确的目的，即保护被解放的奴隶免受白人暴民的伤害。

value.def: If someone or something is free of or free from an unpleasant thing, they do not have it or they are not affected by it.

example.ex: ...a future far more free of fear...
example.tran: 远远摆脱恐惧的未来

example.ex: She retains her slim figure and is free of wrinkles...
example.tran: 她保持着苗条的身材，脸上也没有皱纹。

example.ex: The filtration system provides the crew with clean air free from fumes.
example.tran: 过滤系统使得全体人员能够呼吸到没有烟雾的清新空气。

value.def: A sum of money or type of goods that is free of tax or duty is one that you do not have to pay tax on.
To free someone or something means to make them available for a task or function that they were previously not available for.

example.ex: Toolbelts free both hands and lessen the risk of dropping hammers...
example.tran: 工具腰带解放了双手，还减少了锤子掉落的风险。

example.ex: His deal with Disney will run out shortly, freeing him to pursue his own project...
example.tran: 他和迪斯尼的协议很快就要到期，这样他就可以腾出身来发展自己的项目了。

example.ex: There were more civilians working for the police, freeing officers from desk jobs.
example.tran: 更多的平民在为警察部门工作，使得警员从文案中解脱出来。

example.ex: It can handle even the most complex graphic jobs, freeing up your computer for other tasks.
example.tran: 它可以处理哪怕是最复杂的图形作业，空出计算机以便用于其他任务。

value.def: If you have a free period of time or are free at a particular time, you are not working or occupied then.

example.ex: She spent her free time shopping...
example.tran: 她空闲的时候就去购物。

example.ex: I used to write during my free periods at school...
example.tran: 过去我经常在课余时间写作。

example.ex: I am always free at lunchtime.
example.tran: 午餐时间我总是有空。

value.tran: 空闲的;有空的;不上班的;不在忙的

value.def: If something such as a table or seat is free, it is not being used or occupied by anyone, or is not reserved for anyone to use.

example.ex: There was only one seat free on the train...
example.tran: 列车上只剩下一个空座。

example.ex: They took the only free table, which was just inside the door.
example.tran: 他们在刚进门处的唯一一张空桌子边坐下。

value.tran: 不在用的;无人使用的;未被占用的

value.def: If you get something free or if it gets free, it is no longer trapped by anything or attached to anything.

example.ex: The severe conditions hampered attempts to pull the vessel free of the rig...
example.tran: 恶劣的天气情况使得把那艘船拉离钻塔的努力很难奏效。

example.ex: He pulled his arm free, and strode for the door...
example.tran: 他抽出胳膊，大步朝门走去。

example.ex: The shark was writhing around wildly, trying to get free.
example.tran: 那条鲨鱼疯狂地扭动身体，试图挣脱。

gramarinfo.label: v n ADJ, v-link ADJ, oft ADJ <l>of</l> n

value.tran: 松开的;脱开的;未缚住的;未固定的

value.def: If you free someone or something, you remove them from the place in which they have been trapped or become fixed.

example.ex: It took firemen two hours to cut through the drive belt to free him...
example.tran: 消防员花了两个小时才把传动带切断，把他救了出来。

example.ex: He managed to free one hand to ward off a punch.
example.tran: 他设法挣脱出一只手来挡住了一拳。

value.tran: 松开;解开;使不再缚住(或固定)

value.def: When someone is using one hand or arm to hold or move something, their other hand or arm is referred to as their free one.

example.ex: He snatched up the receiver and his free hand groped for the switch on the bedside lamp...
example.tran: 他一只手抓起电话听筒，另一只手去摸床头灯的开关。

example.ex: She checked her fall with her free arm.
example.tran: 多亏了她还有一只手空着才没让自己倒下去。

value.def: If you say that someone is free with something such as advice or money, you mean that they give a lot of it, sometimes when it is not wanted.

example.ex: They weren't always so free with their advice...
example.tran: 他们并不是一直都如此好为人师。

example.ex: They would often be free with criticism, some of it unjustified.
example.tran: 他们经常会大肆批评，而且其中有些并无道理。

value.tran: 慷慨的;大手大脚的;过分给予的

value.def: You say 'feel free' when you want to give someone permission to do something, in a very willing way.

example.ex: Go right ahead. Feel free...
example.tran: 开始吧。请便。

example.ex: If you have any questions at all, please feel free to ask me.
example.tran: 如果有任何问题，请随意提问。

value.def: If you do something or get something for free, you do it without being paid or get it without having to pay for it.

example.ex: I wasn't expecting you to do it for free...
example.tran: 我并没有指望你白干。

example.ex: Why waste £50 when you could get it for free?
example.tran: 能够免费得到为什么还要浪费50英镑呢？

value.def: You say that you will express a critical opinion about something for free when you want to emphasize how strongly you feel about it.

example.ex: I'll tell you one thing for free: I can't stand him.
example.tran: 不管怎样我都要说：我受不了他。

value.tran: (表达批评意见时用于强调)不管怎样

value.def: To free up a market, economy, or system means to make it operate with fewer restrictions and controls.

example.ex: ...policies for freeing up markets and extending competition.
example.tran: 开放市场、扩大竞争的政策

value.tran: 开放，放开(市场、经济或体系)
